{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1342,"text":"This is my grandfather."},{"time":4162,"text":"And this is my son."},{"time":6506,"text":"My grandfather taught me to work with wood"},{"time":8734,"text":"when I was a little boy,"},{"time":10368,"text":"and he also taught me the idea that"},{"time":12371,"text":"if you cut down a tree\nto turn it into something,"},{"time":15280,"text":"honor that tree's life\nand make it as beautiful"},{"time":17559,"text":"as you possibly can."},{"time":19709,"text":"My little boy reminded me"},{"time":23221,"text":"that for all the technology\nand all the toys in the world,"},{"time":26100,"text":"sometimes just a small block of wood,"},{"time":28490,"text":"if you stack it up tall,"},{"time":30321,"text":"actually is an incredibly inspiring thing."},{"time":34404,"text":"These are my buildings."},{"time":36241,"text":"I build all around the world"},{"time":37961,"text":"out of our office\nin Vancouver and New York."},{"time":40793,"text":"And we build buildings\nof different sizes and styles"},{"time":43554,"text":"and different materials,\ndepending on where we are."},{"time":45580,"text":"But wood is the material\nthat I love the most,"},{"time":47863,"text":"and I'm going to tell you\nthe story about wood."},{"time":49818,"text":"And part of the reason\nI love it is that every time"},{"time":51814,"text":"people go into my buildings that are wood,"},{"time":54107,"text":"I notice they react\ncompletely differently."},{"time":56853,"text":"I've never seen anybody walk\ninto one of my buildings"},{"time":59401,"text":"and hug a steel or a concrete column,"},{"time":61754,"text":"but I've actually seen\nthat happen in a wood building."},{"time":64654,"text":"I've actually seen\nhow people touch the wood,"},{"time":67150,"text":"and I think there's a reason for it."},{"time":69235,"text":"Just like snowflakes,\nno two pieces of wood"},{"time":71741,"text":"can ever be the same anywhere on Earth."},{"time":74425,"text":"That's a wonderful thing."},{"time":76322,"text":"I like to think that wood"},{"time":78858,"text":"gives Mother Nature\nfingerprints in our buildings."},{"time":82419,"text":"It's Mother\nNature's fingerprints that make"},{"time":84505,"text":"our buildings connect us to nature\nin the built environment."},{"time":89151,"text":"Now, I live in Vancouver, near a forest"},{"time":91213,"text":"that grows to 33 stories tall."},{"time":94290,"text":"Down the coast here\nin California, the redwood forest"},{"time":96838,"text":"grows to 40 stories tall."},{"time":99890,"text":"But the buildings\nthat we think about in wood"},{"time":102532,"text":"are only four stories tall\nin most places on Earth."},{"time":105637,"text":"Even building codes actually limit\nthe ability for us to build"},{"time":109358,"text":"much taller than four\nstories in many places,"},{"time":111741,"text":"and that's true here in the United States."},{"time":113765,"text":"Now there are exceptions,"},{"time":115593,"text":"but there needs to be some exceptions,"},{"time":117141,"text":"and things are going\nto change, I'm hoping."},{"time":119213,"text":"And the reason I think that way is that"},{"time":121186,"text":"today half of us live in cities,"},{"time":124310,"text":"and that number is going\nto grow to 75 percent."},{"time":127698,"text":"Cities and density mean that our buildings"},{"time":129783,"text":"are going to continue to be big,"},{"time":132229,"text":"and I think there's a role\nfor wood to play in cities."},{"time":136047,"text":"And I feel that way\nbecause three billion people"},{"time":139203,"text":"in the world today,\nover the next 20 years,"},{"time":142049,"text":"will need a new home."},{"time":143569,"text":"That's 40 percent of the world\nthat are going to need"},{"time":146117,"text":"a new building built for them\nin the next 20 years."},{"time":149202,"text":"Now, one in three people\nliving in cities today"},{"time":151777,"text":"actually live in a slum."},{"time":153627,"text":"That's one billion people\nin the world live in slums."},{"time":156968,"text":"A hundred million people\nin the world are homeless."},{"time":161289,"text":"The scale of the challenge for architects"},{"time":163880,"text":"and for society to deal with in building"},{"time":166021,"text":"is to find a solution\nto house these people."},{"time":170615,"text":"But the challenge is,\nas we move to cities,"},{"time":174095,"text":"cities are built in these two materials,"},{"time":177084,"text":"steel and concrete,\nand they're great materials."},{"time":180330,"text":"They're the materials of the last century."},{"time":182432,"text":"But they're also materials\nwith very high energy"},{"time":185021,"text":"and very high greenhouse gas\nemissions in their process."},{"time":189340,"text":"Steel represents about three percent"},{"time":191615,"text":"of man's greenhouse gas emissions,"},{"time":193935,"text":"and concrete is over five percent."},{"time":196536,"text":"So if you think about that, eight percent"},{"time":199150,"text":"of our contribution\nto greenhouse gases today"},{"time":202567,"text":"comes from those two materials alone."},{"time":205735,"text":"We don't think about it\na lot, and unfortunately,"},{"time":208151,"text":"we actually don't even think\nabout buildings, I think,"},{"time":210747,"text":"as much as we should."},{"time":211947,"text":"This is a U.S. statistic\nabout the impact of greenhouse gases."},{"time":215567,"text":"Almost half of our greenhouse gases\nare related to the building industry,"},{"time":218833,"text":"and if we look at energy,\nit's the same story."},{"time":221120,"text":"You'll notice that transportation's sort\nof second down that list,"},{"time":224287,"text":"but that's the conversation\nwe mostly hear about."},{"time":226977,"text":"And although a lot\nof that is about energy,"},{"time":230543,"text":"it's also so much about carbon."},{"time":233424,"text":"The problem I see is that, ultimately,"},{"time":236407,"text":"the clash of how we solve that problem"},{"time":238714,"text":"of serving those three billion people\nthat need a home,"},{"time":241982,"text":"and climate change,\nare a head-on collision"},{"time":245454,"text":"about to happen, or already happening."},{"time":248407,"text":"That challenge means that we have\nto start thinking in new ways,"},{"time":251118,"text":"and I think wood is going\nto be part of that solution,"},{"time":253714,"text":"and I'm going to tell\nyou the story of why."},{"time":255300,"text":"As an architect, wood\nis the only material,"},{"time":257714,"text":"big material, that I can build with"},{"time":260130,"text":"that's already grown\nby the power of the sun."},{"time":263100,"text":"When a tree grows in the forest\nand gives off oxygen"},{"time":266878,"text":"and soaks up carbon dioxide,"},{"time":268975,"text":"and it dies and it falls\nto the forest floor,"},{"time":271941,"text":"it gives that carbon dioxide back\nto the atmosphere or into the ground."},{"time":276246,"text":"If it burns in a forest fire,\nit's going to give that carbon"},{"time":279216,"text":"back to the atmosphere as well."},{"time":281652,"text":"But if you take that wood\nand you put it into a building"},{"time":284696,"text":"or into a piece of furniture\nor into that wooden toy,"},{"time":288032,"text":"it actually has an amazing capacity"},{"time":289723,"text":"to store the carbon and provide\nus with a sequestration."},{"time":293878,"text":"One cubic meter of wood will store"},{"time":297157,"text":"one tonne of carbon dioxide."},{"time":299923,"text":"Now our two solutions\nto climate are obviously"},{"time":302138,"text":"to reduce our emissions and find storage."},{"time":304674,"text":"Wood is the only major\nmaterial building material"},{"time":307032,"text":"I can build with that actually\ndoes both those two things."},{"time":310632,"text":"So I believe that we have"},{"time":313733,"text":"an ethic that the Earth grows our food,"},{"time":316285,"text":"and we need to move\nto an ethic in this century"},{"time":318548,"text":"that the Earth should grow our homes."},{"time":321229,"text":"Now, how are we going to do that"},{"time":322798,"text":"when we're urbanizing at this rate"},{"time":324088,"text":"and we think about wood\nbuildings only at four stories?"},{"time":326688,"text":"We need to reduce the concrete\nand steel and we need"},{"time":329189,"text":"to grow bigger,\nand what we've been working on"},{"time":331404,"text":"is 30-story tall buildings made of wood."},{"time":335752,"text":"We've been engineering\nthem with an engineer"},{"time":339350,"text":"named Eric Karsh who works with me on it,"},{"time":341800,"text":"and we've been doing this new work because"},{"time":344113,"text":"there are new wood products\nout there for us to use,"},{"time":346658,"text":"and we call them mass timber panels."},{"time":348880,"text":"These are panels made with young trees,"},{"time":351203,"text":"small growth trees, small pieces of wood"},{"time":354845,"text":"glued together to make\npanels that are enormous:"},{"time":357364,"text":"eight feet wide, 64 feet long,\nand of various thicknesses."},{"time":361719,"text":"The way I describe this\nbest, I've found, is to say"},{"time":364858,"text":"that we're all used\nto two-by-four construction"},{"time":367121,"text":"when we think about wood."},{"time":368128,"text":"That's what people jump\nto as a conclusion."},{"time":370447,"text":"Two-by-four construction\nis sort of like the little"},{"time":372319,"text":"eight-dot bricks of Lego\nthat we all played with as kids,"},{"time":375058,"text":"and you can make all kinds\nof cool things out of Lego"},{"time":377995,"text":"at that size, and out of two-by-fours."},{"time":380914,"text":"But do remember when you were a kid,"},{"time":381782,"text":"and you kind of sifted\nthrough the pile in your basement,"},{"time":384521,"text":"and you found that big\n24-dot brick of Lego,"},{"time":386655,"text":"and you were kind of like,"},{"time":387490,"text":"\"Cool, this is awesome. I can\nbuild something really big,"},{"time":389644,"text":"and this is going to be great.\""},{"time":391223,"text":"That's the change."},{"time":392566,"text":"Mass timber panels\nare those 24-dot bricks."},{"time":395512,"text":"They're changing the scale\nof what we can do,"},{"time":397213,"text":"and what we've developed\nis something we call FFTT,"},{"time":399886,"text":"which is a Creative Commons solution"},{"time":402340,"text":"to building a very flexible system"},{"time":407255,"text":"of building with these large\npanels where we tilt up"},{"time":409938,"text":"six stories at a time if we want to."},{"time":413797,"text":"This animation shows you\nhow the building goes together"},{"time":417413,"text":"in a very simple way, but these\nbuildings are available"},{"time":420969,"text":"for architects and engineers\nnow to build on"},{"time":423222,"text":"for different cultures in the world,"},{"time":424961,"text":"different architectural\nstyles and characters."},{"time":427564,"text":"In order for us to build safely,"},{"time":430366,"text":"we've engineered these\nbuildings, actually,"},{"time":432566,"text":"to work in a Vancouver context,"},{"time":434286,"text":"where we're a high seismic zone,"},{"time":435834,"text":"even at 30 stories tall."},{"time":439005,"text":"Now obviously, every time I bring this up,"},{"time":440927,"text":"people even, you know, here\nat the conference, say,"},{"time":442891,"text":"\"Are you serious? Thirty stories?\nHow's that going to happen?\""},{"time":445868,"text":"And there's a lot of really\ngood questions that are asked"},{"time":449275,"text":"and important questions\nthat we spent quite a long time"},{"time":451082,"text":"working on the answers\nto as we put together"},{"time":453461,"text":"our report and the peer reviewed report."},{"time":456034,"text":"I'm just going to focus on a few of them,"},{"time":457618,"text":"and let's start with fire,\nbecause I think fire"},{"time":459127,"text":"is probably the first one that you're\nall thinking about right now."},{"time":462342,"text":"Fair enough."},{"time":462945,"text":"And the way I describe it is this."},{"time":464638,"text":"If I asked you to take\na match and light it"},{"time":466833,"text":"and hold up a log and try\nto get that log to go on fire,"},{"time":470821,"text":"it doesn't happen, right?\nWe all know that."},{"time":472620,"text":"But to build a fire, you kind\nof start with small pieces"},{"time":475393,"text":"of wood and you work your way up,"},{"time":476989,"text":"and eventually you can\nadd the log to the fire,"},{"time":479636,"text":"and when you do add the log\nto the fire, of course,"},{"time":482089,"text":"it burns, but it burns slowly."},{"time":484621,"text":"Well, mass timber panels,\nthese new products"},{"time":486741,"text":"that we're using, are much like the log."},{"time":488988,"text":"It's hard to start them\non fire, and when they do,"},{"time":491683,"text":"they actually burn\nextraordinarily predictably,"},{"time":494300,"text":"and we can use fire science\nin order to predict"},{"time":496652,"text":"and make these buildings\nas safe as concrete"},{"time":498772,"text":"and as safe as steel."},{"time":501360,"text":"The next big issue, deforestation."},{"time":504125,"text":"Eighteen percent of our contribution"},{"time":506595,"text":"to greenhouse gas emissions worldwide"},{"time":508680,"text":"is the result of deforestation."},{"time":510181,"text":"The last thing we want\nto do is cut down trees."},{"time":513623,"text":"Or, the last thing we want to do\nis cut down the wrong trees."},{"time":517820,"text":"There are models for sustainable forestry"},{"time":520761,"text":"that allow us to cut trees properly,"},{"time":522933,"text":"and those are the only trees appropriate"},{"time":524862,"text":"to use for these kinds of systems."},{"time":526583,"text":"Now I actually think that these ideas"},{"time":528712,"text":"will change the economics\nof deforestation."},{"time":532290,"text":"In countries with deforestation issues,"},{"time":534391,"text":"we need to find a way to provide"},{"time":536875,"text":"better value for the forest"},{"time":539341,"text":"and actually encourage\npeople to make money"},{"time":541725,"text":"through very fast growth cycles --"},{"time":543603,"text":"10-, 12-, 15-year-old trees\nthat make these products"},{"time":546574,"text":"and allow us to build at this scale."},{"time":548973,"text":"We've calculated a 20-story building:"},{"time":551174,"text":"We'll grow enough wood in North\nAmerica every 13 minutes."},{"time":554461,"text":"That's how much it takes."},{"time":556903,"text":"The carbon story here\nis a really good one."},{"time":559672,"text":"If we built a 20-story building\nout of cement and concrete,"},{"time":563274,"text":"the process would result\nin the manufacturing"},{"time":565747,"text":"of that cement and 1,200\ntonnes of carbon dioxide."},{"time":569712,"text":"If we did it in wood, in this solution,"},{"time":572016,"text":"we'd sequester about 3,100 tonnes,"},{"time":573919,"text":"for a net difference of 4,300 tonnes."},{"time":576619,"text":"That's the equivalent of about 900 cars"},{"time":579296,"text":"removed from the road in one year."},{"time":582033,"text":"Think back to that three billion people"},{"time":583915,"text":"that need a new home,"},{"time":585154,"text":"and maybe this\nis a contributor to reducing."},{"time":588226,"text":"We're at the beginning\nof a revolution, I hope,"},{"time":590907,"text":"in the way we build, because this\nis the first new way"},{"time":593503,"text":"to build a skyscraper\nin probably 100 years or more."},{"time":597932,"text":"But the challenge is changing\nsociety's perception"},{"time":600455,"text":"of possibility, and it's a huge challenge."},{"time":602479,"text":"The engineering is, truthfully,\nthe easy part of this."},{"time":605988,"text":"And the way I describe it is this."},{"time":608005,"text":"The first skyscraper, technically --"},{"time":610165,"text":"and the definition of a skyscraper is 10\nstories tall, believe it or not —"},{"time":612715,"text":"but the first skyscraper\nwas this one in Chicago,"},{"time":615073,"text":"and people were terrified to walk\nunderneath this building."},{"time":618028,"text":"But only four years after it was built,"},{"time":619968,"text":"Gustave Eiffel was building\nthe Eiffel Tower,"},{"time":622594,"text":"and as he built the Eiffel Tower,"},{"time":624190,"text":"he changed the skylines\nof the cities of the world,"},{"time":628797,"text":"changed and created a competition"},{"time":631869,"text":"between places like New\nYork City and Chicago,"},{"time":634084,"text":"where developers started building\nbigger and bigger buildings"},{"time":637013,"text":"and pushing the envelope\nup higher and higher"},{"time":640294,"text":"with better and better engineering."},{"time":642394,"text":"We built this model in New York, actually,"},{"time":644428,"text":"as a theoretical model on the campus"},{"time":647215,"text":"of a technical university soon to come,"},{"time":649563,"text":"and the reason we picked this site"},{"time":651414,"text":"to just show you what these\nbuildings may look like,"},{"time":654151,"text":"because the exterior can change."},{"time":655938,"text":"It's really just the structure\nthat we're talking about."},{"time":658671,"text":"The reason we picked it is because this\nis a technical university,"},{"time":661838,"text":"and I believe that wood is the most"},{"time":663680,"text":"technologically advanced\nmaterial I can build with."},{"time":667320,"text":"It just happens to be that Mother\nNature holds the patent,"},{"time":670121,"text":"and we don't really feel\ncomfortable with it."},{"time":672812,"text":"But that's the way it should be,"},{"time":674656,"text":"nature's fingerprints\nin the built environment."},{"time":678451,"text":"I'm looking for this opportunity"},{"time":680370,"text":"to create an Eiffel Tower\nmoment, we call it."},{"time":683560,"text":"Buildings are starting\nto go up around the world."},{"time":685600,"text":"There's a building in London\nthat's nine stories,"},{"time":687481,"text":"a new building that just\nfinished in Australia"},{"time":689864,"text":"that I believe is 10 or 11."},{"time":691821,"text":"We're starting to push the height\nup of these wood buildings,"},{"time":695368,"text":"and we're hoping, and I'm hoping,"},{"time":697173,"text":"that my hometown of Vancouver\nactually potentially"},{"time":700185,"text":"announces the world's tallest\nat around 20 stories"},{"time":702855,"text":"in the not-so-distant future."},{"time":705538,"text":"That Eiffel Tower moment\nwill break the ceiling,"},{"time":708268,"text":"these arbitrary ceilings of height,"},{"time":709959,"text":"and allow wood buildings\nto join the competition."},{"time":712651,"text":"And I believe the race is ultimately on."},{"time":714616,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":716066,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}